# Aside Preferences

> Generated by kimi-agent-kit install. Edit freely; uninstall preserves this file since it is signed as user-owned (`kimi-agent-kit-custom:aside-prefs`).

## Preferred third-party advisor

Default backend when Kimi Code CLI decides to ask a cross-family advisor: **@@ASIDE_PREFERRED@@**

Valid values: `none` | `codex` | `copilot`

## Default models (per backend)

When Kimi Code CLI calls an aside tool and the user has not named a specific model for this turn, pass these values as the tool's `model` param. Leave blank to let each CLI use its own default.

- codex default model: **@@ASIDE_CODEX_MODEL@@**
- copilot default model: **@@ASIDE_COPILOT_MODEL@@**

## Default reasoning effort (per backend)

For CLIs that expose a reasoning-effort knob. Passed as the tool's `reasoning_effort` param when unset for the current turn.

- codex default reasoning effort: **@@ASIDE_CODEX_EFFORT@@**   (`low` / `medium` / `high` / `xhigh`, or blank)
- copilot default reasoning effort: **@@ASIDE_COPILOT_EFFORT@@** (`low` / `medium` / `high` / `xhigh`, or blank — maps to `copilot --effort`)

## Default model fallback chain (per backend)

Passed as `model_fallback` when you have not named a chain for the turn. A
transient backend failure (rate limit, quota, model unavailable) automatically
retries the SAME question against the next model in this list, in order; a
non-transient failure (e.g. auth/permission) is never retried.

- codex default model fallback: **@@ASIDE_CODEX_FALLBACK@@**   (comma-separated; blank = none)
- copilot default model fallback: **@@ASIDE_COPILOT_FALLBACK@@** (comma-separated; blank = none)

## Auto-call policy

**@@ASIDE_POLICY@@**

Valid values:
- `conservative` — only call aside tools on explicit user request (default when this file is absent).
- `preference-only` — call the preferred backend on explicit user request; no auto-calls.
- `proactive` — on high-stakes decisions (architecture changes, cross-module refactors, concurrency / invariant changes, API / schema / public-contract changes, security-sensitive code) the agent **SHOULD** call the preferred backend even without being asked. Trigger list and cost carve-out live in `kimi-agent-kit--aside.md`.

## Notes

Free-form. Read this file before any aside call. Keep it short so it stays in active context. Anything you write here is treated as a live rule; there are no templates or placeholders to disambiguate.
